Description: Small rounded clay seal-impression that shows shallow impressions on the rear that might originate from a basket? The fine dark brown Nile clay has inclusions of mica and was hardened after excavation. The top shows five parallel impressions of a turned string all the way along the sealing. Maybe this method was used as substitution for a real seal?
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
